Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  named Michael Muntner and Charlie Newton as co-heads of its Americas health-
care banking team.  The appointments are effective immediately, according to a
memo obtained by Bloomberg News. A spokesman for Credit Suisse
confirmed the memoâ€™s contents.  Muntner advised Express Scripts Holding Co. on its $29
billion acquisition of Medco Health Solutions Inc. announced in
2011 and helped to raise financing. Newton advised drugmaker
Amylin Pharmaceuticals Inc. when the company was sold last year
to Bristol-Myers Squibb Co. for $5.3 billion.  They will report to Tom Davidson and Stuart Smith, global
co-heads of health-care banking.  To contact the reporter on this story:
